'''Senjitsu''' (選日) refers to a system of determining auspicious and inauspicious days based on combinations of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|干支|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} in {{ill|Calendar annotations|ja|暦注|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. It is a general term that includes {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Seven-day week|ja|七曜|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Jūniji|ja|十二直|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} (middle tier), {{ill|Twenty-eight mansions|ja|二十八宿|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Nine Star Ki|ja|九星|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, and {{ill|Lower-tier calendar annotations|ja|暦注下段|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, among others. It is also called '''Taku-jitsu''' (擇日), '''Senjitsu''' (撰日), or '''Zasshū''' (雑注). The method of determining dates in calendar annotations is called {{ill|Senjitsu-hō|ja|撰日法|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. Many aspects of this system overlap with the contents of the ancient Chinese "[[:zh:萬年曆|Wànniánlì]]" (or ''Wànnián {{ill|Nongminli|ja|中国暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}''), leading to the belief that it originates from the farmers' almanac<ref>{{Cite web |title=查詢農民曆─農民曆/農曆/黃曆｜科技紫微網 |url=https://ecal.click108.com.twindex.php/ |website=ecal.click108.com.twindex.php |access-date=2023-07-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=2023農民曆吉時查詢、黃曆通書黃道吉日查詢 - 農民曆查詢 |url=http://www.nongli.info/huangli/ |website=www.nongli.info |access-date=2023-07-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=子易預測網 - 擇日萬年曆 |url=https://forecasting.hk/calendar/ |website=forecasting.hk |access-date=2023-07-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=農民曆專有名詞 @ Gloria隨筆 :: 痞客邦 :: |url=http://andafansia.pixnet.net/blog/post/40052541 |website=Gloria隨筆 |date=2011-12-11 |access-date=2023-07-20 |language=zh-TW |last=Andafansia (Andafansia)}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=你應該懂的農民曆常識!搞懂「當日紀要」神祉、挑對日子趨吉避凶不求人 {{!}} 食尚玩家 |url=https://supertaste.tvbs.com.tw/hot/321211 |website=TVBS |date=2020-02-06 |access-date=2023-07-20 |last=TVBS}}</ref>. However, some aspects such as {{ill|Ichiryū Manbai Day|ja|一粒万倍日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} were independently created in Japan after the introduction of the farmers' almanac and lack historical credibility, as they do not exist in the original almanac.
== List == * {{ill|Ichiryū Manbai Day|ja|一粒万倍日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} * {{ill|Fujōju Day|ja|不成就日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} * {{ill|Hassen|ja|八専|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} * {{ill|Jippōkure|ja|十方暮|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} * {{ill|Ten'ichijin|ja|天一神|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} (Ten'ichitenjō) * {{ill|Sanrimbō|ja|三隣亡|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} * {{ill|Sanpuku|ja|三伏|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} * {{ill|Hando|ja|犯土|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} (Ōdo and Shōdo) * {{ill|Rōjitsu|ja|臘日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} * Others ({{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Seven-day week|ja|七曜|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Jūniji|ja|十二直|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Twenty-eight mansions|ja|二十八宿|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Nine Star Ki|ja|九星|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Lower-tier calendar annotations|ja|暦注下段|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}})
Among these, Ichiryū Manbai Day, Fujōju Day, Sanrimbō, and {{ill|Tensha Day|ja|天赦日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} (although it originally belongs to the lower-tier calendar annotations, it is sometimes categorized under Senjitsu) are relatively well-known and are often included in {{ill|Perpetual calendar|ja|七曜表|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}-style calendars with sufficient detail. On the other hand, minor annotations such as Hassen, Jippōkure, Ten'ichitenjō, and Hando are rarely found in modern Japanese perpetual calendars due to their lower recognition.
