== List == * {{ill|Ichiryū Manbai Day|ja|一粒万倍日|qq=draft|qq=}} * {{ill|Fujōju Day|ja|不成就日|qq=draft|qq=}} * {{ill|Hassen|ja|八専|qq=draft|qq=}} * {{ill|Jippōkure|ja|十方暮|qq=draft|qq=}} * {{ill|Ten'ichijin|ja|天一神|qq=draft|qq=}} (Ten'ichitenjō) * {{ill|Sanrimbō|ja|三隣亡|qq=draft|qq=}} * {{ill|Sanpuku|ja|三伏|qq=draft|qq=}} * {{ill|Hando|ja|犯土|qq=draft|qq=}} (Ōdo and Shōdo) * {{ill|Rōjitsu|ja|臘日|qq=draft|qq=}} * Others ({{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=draft|qq=}}, {{ill|Seven-day week|ja|七曜|qq=draft|qq=}}, {{ill|Jūniji|ja|十二直|qq=draft|qq=}}, {{ill|Twenty-eight mansions|ja|二十八宿|qq=draft|qq=}}, {{ill|Nine Star Ki|ja|九星|qq=draft|qq=}}, {{ill|Lower-tier calendar annotations|ja|暦注下段|qq=draft|qq=}})
Among these, Ichiryū Manbai Day, Fujōju Day, Sanrimbō, and {{ill|Tensha Day|ja|天赦日|qq=draft|qq=}} (although it originally belongs to the lower-tier calendar annotations, it is sometimes categorized under Senjitsu) are relatively well-known and are often included in {{ill|Perpetual calendar|ja|七曜表|qq=draft|qq=}}-style calendars with sufficient detail. On the other hand, minor annotations such as Hassen, Jippōkure, Ten'ichitenjō, and Hando are rarely found in modern Japanese perpetual calendars due to their lower recognition.
