{{afc comment|Wikidata entry [[Category:Has wikidata]][[d:Q60988968]] Wikidata name: [[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 09:11, 11 June 2025 (UTC)}} '''Senjitsu''' (選日) refers to a system of determining auspicious and inauspicious days based on combinations of the [[:en:Sexagenary cycle|Sexagenary cycle]] in {{ill|rekichū|ja|暦注|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/rekichū|qq=}}. It is a general term that includes {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}}, [[:en:Classical planet|Seven-day week]], {{ill|Jūniji|ja|十二直|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jūniji|qq=|1=Twelve Directions|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11404810}} (middle tier), [[:en:Twenty-Eight Mansions|Twenty-eight mansions]], {{ill|Nine Star Ki|ja|九星|1=Nine Stars|2=ja|3=九星|lt=Nine Stars|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nine Star Ki|qq=}}, and {{ill|Lower-tier calendar annotations|ja|暦注下段|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Lower-tier calendar annotations|qq=|1=rekichuugedan|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11514957}}, among others. It is also called '''Taku-jitsu''' (擇日), '''Senjitsu''' (撰日), or '''Zasshū''' (雑注). The method of determining dates in calendar annotations is called {{ill|Senjitsu-hō|ja|撰日法|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Senjitsu-hō|qq=|1=Senpō|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11498765}}. Many aspects of this system overlap with the contents of the ancient Chinese "[[:zh:萬年曆|Wànniánlì]]" (or ''Wànnián [[:en:Chinese calendar|Nongminli]]''), leading to the belief that it originates from the farmers' almanac<ref>{{Cite web |title=查詢農民曆─農民曆/農曆/黃曆｜科技紫微網 |url=https://ecal.click108.com.twindex.php/ |website=ecal.click108.com.twindex.php |access-date=2023-07-20|qq=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=2023農民曆吉時查詢、黃曆通書黃道吉日查詢 - 農民曆查詢 |url=http://www.nongli.info/huangli/ |website=www.nongli.info |access-date=2023-07-20|qq=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=子易預測網 - 擇日萬年曆 |url=https://